    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Fuel and High-pressure Oil Systems
        - Installation - Fuel Filter Header Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Fuel Filter Header Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f3350007175" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK11/K11002.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Fuel filter header</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 75 bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 oil filler tube support nut (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M10 sensor harness retaining nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel outlet fitting (return to tank)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel pump outlet tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water drain valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Fuel Pressure (EFP) sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water In Fuel (WIF) sensor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">M8 sensor harness retaining nut</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel heater (optional)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel pump inlet tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel inlet fitting (from tank)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Priming pump assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para id="s0722" count="1">Install a new irregular molded gasket between the fuel filter header and intake
                manifold. Position fuel filter header assembly on the intake manifold.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install three M8 x 75 stud bolts and one M8 x 75 bolt holding fuel filter header to the
                intake manifold and tighten bolts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_190.xml" xrefid="t335000702" appearance="hottext">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000702"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install flat washer, sensor harness, and M8 nut on lower front M8 x 75 stud bolt (Item 9).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install M10 nut holding sensor harness to the intake manifold stud bolt under the fuel
                filter header (Item 3).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten M8 and M10 sensor harness retaining nuts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_SAPPB01.xml" xrefid="sAppB01">standard torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="sAppB01"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filler tube support, two M8 nuts, and one M6 x 16 bolt holding the oil filler
                tube support to the fuel filter header.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten M6 x 16 bolt to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_427.xml" xrefid="t335001602">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001602"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten two M8 nuts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_427.xml" xrefid="t335001602">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001602"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f3350007209" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figK11/K11033.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Low-pressure fuel pump inlet and outlet tube assemblies</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">3/8 tube sleeve (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Coupling nut (4)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel pump outlet tube assembly</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Low-pressure fuel pump inlet tube assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two new 3/8 tube sleeves onto ends of both the low-pressure fuel pump inlet and
                outlet tube assemblies.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install low-pressure fuel pump inlet tube assembly ends into the fuel filter header and
                low-pressure fuel pump and tighten coupling nuts to
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_190.xml" xrefid="t335000702">special torque</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335000702"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install low-pressure fuel pump outlet tube assembly ends into the fuel filter header and
                low-pressure fuel pump and tighten nuts to special torque.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the fuel return and inlet lines.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_424.xml" xrefid="s1627">Oil Level Gauge Assembly</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s1627"/>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the IPR valve, fuel heater, WIF sensor, and EFP sensor harness connectors.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">See
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_167.xml" xrefid="s0704">Priming Fuel System</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="s0704"/>
                to purge air out of fuel system to start engine.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
